# Operation

## Contract

- Suffix **`Operation`**; **one** method **`execute(...)`** with explicit inputs.
- **tsyringe** **`@singleton()`**; inject gateways, services, state setter/getters as **concrete types** — no string or symbol tokens.
- **Only** layer for **business logic** and **state mutation** (via setters).
- May call **gateways** and **services**; **must not** call another operation.
- Prefer **inputs from controller** over reading global state inside `execute` (keep reusable).

## Scope

- **One** logical atomic change; one primary entity (batch OK when inherently single action, e.g. token set).

## Callers

- **Controllers** only (not handlers, components, or other operations).

## Good / bad

| Good | Bad |
|------|-----|
| `DeleteCatalogOperation.execute({ catalogId })` | Operation calls `otherOp.execute` |
| Operation uses state setter after gateway load | Controller writes slice |
